">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"til.simonwillison.net\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1b84507d70afa509\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - coollabsio/openclaw: Fully featured & automated OpenClaw docker images\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1b84507d70afa509\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/coollabsio/openclaw\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c4227f060e0582c1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFully featured &amp; automated OpenClaw docker images. Contribute to coollabsio/openclaw development by creating an account on GitHub.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c4227f060e0582c1\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"faf79990cf4b979b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDocker - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"faf79990cf4b979b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/install/docker\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e699c425af38f83\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe image runs as <strong>node (uid 1000).</strong> If you see permission errors on /home/node/.openclaw, make sure your host bind mounts are owned by uid 1000. Example (Linux host): ... If you choose to run as root for convenience, you accept the security tradeoff.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e699c425af38f83\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bbf0a8fd0ce35d64\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw Docker: How to Run OpenClaw in a Container (2026)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bbf0a8fd0ce35d64\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://boilerplatehub.com/blog/openclaw-docker\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2d3451391f61d9f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nYes. <strong>The alpine/openclaw image on Docker Hub is the official distribution</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2d3451391f61d9f\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 days ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"boilerplatehub.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"openclaw docker hub official image","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":928,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3243d300622b401\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nalpine/openclaw - Docker Image\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3243d300622b401\">>>","url":"https://hub.docker.com/r/alpine/openclaw","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d514d8e046a779f9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe image is automatically mirrored from the official source at ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw · I’m actively working on resolving this and build on alpine · https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/alpine/openclaw/tags⁠\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d514d8e046a779f9\">>>","siteName":"hub.docker.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"007d7d1282e2f95a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRunning OpenClaw in Docker | Simon Willison’s TILs\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"007d7d1282e2f95a\">>>","url":"https://til.simonwillison.net/llms/openclaw-docker","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3229dc0c765cc7f6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMine is running the image <strong>openclaw:local</strong> and has a container name openclaw-openclaw-gateway-1. The other container provided by Docker Compose is called openclaw-cli and can be used to run the openclaw CLI commands for managing the instance.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3229dc0c765cc7f6\">>>","siteName":"til.simonwillison.net"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1b84507d70afa509\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - coollabsio/openclaw: Fully featured & automated OpenClaw docker images\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_