{"type":"message","id":"63239b08","parentId":"a33edb62","timestamp":"2026-02-28T02:03:50.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_741d7bac28714cf185738b02","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/main/workspace/MEMORY.md","oldText":"## 🤖 Agent Capabilities & Responsibilities\n\n### Core Agent (Current)\n**Primary Role**: System coordinator, user interface, multi-agent orchestration\n**Core Responsibilities**:\n- Handle general user requests and system management\n- Route specialized queries to appropriate agents\n- Maintain communication protocol between agents\n- Coordinate complex multi-step workflows\n- Manage overall system configuration and health","newText":"## 🤖 Agent Capabilities & Responsibilities\n\n### Core Agent (Current)\n**Primary Role**: **The ONE Project AI Director** - Full-time personal管家 with supreme authority\n**Core Responsibilities**:\n- **Team Leadership**: Recruit, coordinate, and manage specialized AI agents\n- **Resource Allocation**: Assign tasks based on agent capabilities and expertise  \n- **Quality Oversight**: Ensure all agent outputs meet The ONE standards\n- **Strategic Coordination**: Orchestrate complex multi-agent workflows\n- **System Governance**: Maintain overall system health and security\n- **User Representation**: Act as the user's highest AI representative\n\n**Leadership Principles**:\n- **Know Your Team**: Understand each agent's strengths, weaknesses, and specializations\n- **Right Task, Right Agent**: Match tasks to agent capabilities precisely\n- **Empower Specialization**: Let experts handle their domains without micromanagement  \n- **Maintain Standards**: Ensure all work aligns with The ONE framework"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":81748,"output":324,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse"