{"type":"message","id":"6be0154b","parentId":"da793033","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:38:41.112Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ae1315cc5da740d59ec4f305","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"openclaw multiple telegram bots same group different responses\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1220,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09c3721ec1ece14e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTelegram - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09c3721ec1ece14e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/telegram\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3b399fb60997c37a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAdmin status is controlled in Telegram group settings.Admin bots receive all group messages, which is useful for always-on group behavior.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3b399fb60997c37a\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2abc41827c0ca78\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMessage Processing Bottleneck with Multiple Telegram Bots (main lane concurrency limit) · Issue #16055 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2abc41827c0ca78\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/16055\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14617ddd707a5a51\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWhen sending messages to multiple agents simultaneously, <strong>responses are delayed by 1-2 minutes</strong>. Investigation reveals that all messages are processed serially through a shared queue, even though each agent is configured as an independent bot.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14617ddd707a5a51\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"592c427785661f71\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBug: hasBotMention substring match causes cross-bot mention collision in Telegram multi-account groups · Issue #29173 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"592c427785661f71\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/29173\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"754e6a927d8f34da\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDescription When running multiple Telegram bot accounts in the same group, <strong>hasBotMention() in send-CpkY_YZv</strong>.js uses String.includes() for mention detection, which matches substrings instead of exact usernames. This causes a bot to incorr...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"754e6a927d8f34da\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"5 hours ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7de34a47a0dde3c8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMulti-account Telegram: only default bot receives messages · Issue #19000 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7de34a47a0dde3c8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/19000\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d3c59264f816d163\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBug Description When using multiple Telegram bot accounts bound to different agents via bindings, <strong>only the default Telegram account receives messages</strong>. The second account receives updates from Telegram API but messages are not routed to t...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d3c59264f816d163\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5fa39690fad36bf0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Bug]: Bots can't read other bot's messages on Telegram · Issue #408 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5fa39690fad36bf0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/408\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b0042fdb90ae19a4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSummary When running Clawdbot on Telegram in a group, <strong>the bot does not receive updates for messages authored by other bots in the same group</strong> — even if: Clawdbot is a group admin, and/or privacy mode is disabled. This is surprising if you...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b0042fdb90ae19a4\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"January 7, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"openclaw multiple telegram bots same group different responses","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1220,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09c3721ec1ece14e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTelegram - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09c3721ec1ece14e\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/telegram","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3b399fb60997c37a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAdmin status is controlled in Telegram group settings.Admin bots receive all group messages, which is useful for always-on group behavior.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3b399fb60997c37a\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d2abc41827c0ca78\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMessage Processing Bottleneck with Multiple Telegram Bots (main lane concurrency limit) · Issue #16055 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d2abc41827c0ca78\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/16055","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14617ddd707a5a51\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWhen sending messages to multiple agents simultaneously, <strong>responses are delayed by 1-2 minutes</strong>. Investigation reveals that all messages are processed serially through a shared queue, even though each agent is configured as an independent bot.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14617ddd707a5a51\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"592c427785661f71\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBug: hasBotMention substring match causes cross-bot mention collision in Telegram multi-account groups · Issue #29173 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"592c427785661f71\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/29173","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"754e6a927d8f34da\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDescription When running multiple Telegram bot accounts in the same group, <strong>hasBotMention() in send-CpkY_YZv</strong>.js uses String.includes() for mention detection, which matches substrings instead of exact usernames. This causes a bot to incorr...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"754e6a927d8f34da\">>>","published":"5 hours ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7de34a47a0dde3c8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMulti-account Telegram: only default bot receives messages · Issue #19000 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7de34a47a0dde3c8\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/19000","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3c59264f816d163\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBug Description When using multiple Telegram bot accounts bound to different agents via bindings, <strong>only the default Telegram account receives messages</strong>. The second account receives updates from Telegram API but messages are not routed to t...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3c59264f816d163\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago