{"type":"message","id":"5beda811","parentId":"5ee3df85","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:52:35.170Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bb6a7ba0c5f84988b27868fb","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"openclaw multi agent telegram same group mention routing\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 965,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee6a683b4df2f0b6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMulti-Agent Routing - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee6a683b4df2f0b6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/multi-agent\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36b4d3ddc56ac3a4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFor shared groups, <strong>bind the group to one agent or use Broadcast groups</strong>. Bindings are deterministic and most-specific wins: ... fallback to default agent (agents.list[].default, else first list entry, default: main) If multiple bindings match ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"36b4d3ddc56ac3a4\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a9467202c23698d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBuild a Multi-Agent OpenClaw Team in Telegram — With a Single Gateway\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a9467202c23698d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://zerofuturetech.substack.com/p/build-a-multi-agent-openclaw-team\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0b7ae050e9d4bde\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe accountId here should be set ... configuration. The first rule is that by default, <strong>all groups require an @mention of a specific target before the agent replies</strong>....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0b7ae050e9d4bde\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"6 days ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"zerofuturetech.substack.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4e23d0917230fbd8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw multi-agent setup with multiple AI assistants - LumaDock\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4e23d0917230fbd8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://lumadock.com/tutorials/openclaw-multi-agent-setup\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e80828cd726c315d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBindings are the deterministic routing rules that tell OpenClaw which agent should handle an incoming message. The binding match rules are strict and they usually follow a “most specific wins” concept, which is what you want. ... The general rule that avoids surprises is: put the most specific bindings first. If you define “all WhatsApp goes to main” and you also define “this specific group goes to work” then put the group binding above the channel-wide binding.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e80828cd726c315d\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"lumadock.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fe91bc12334baa31\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw Telegram Bot Setup: Commands, Routing, and Multi-Agent Sessions - Macaron\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fe91bc12334baa31\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://macaron.im/blog/openclaw-telegram-bot-setup\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"faf3e875161b9b9a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEvery OpenClaw Telegram setup starts with @BotFather, Telegram&#x27;s official bot creation interface. This hasn&#x27;t changed since Telegram launched bots — it&#x27;s still the only way to generate API tokens. ... /setjoingroups → Allow/deny adding bot to groups /setprivacy → OFF = bot sees all group messages ON = bot only sees mentions and commands\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"faf3e875161b9b9a\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"macaron.im\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"85a6ea632cd15f08\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nmulti-agent setup on telegram - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"85a6ea632cd15f08\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1470099431842906192\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"32843f17706ff086\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHi, I want to make a multi-agent setup on a Telegram group. My goal is to add my main bot and all worker bots in one place in t he telegram bot. The task is to talk to the main bot, who asks tasks to the other bot, who has specific knowledge for those jobs. Once the job is done, he will take ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"32843f17706ff086\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.answeroverflow.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"openclaw multi agent telegram same group mention routing","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":965,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee6a683b4df2f0b6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMulti-Agent Routing - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee6a683b4df2f0b6\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/multi-agent","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36b4d3ddc56ac3a4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFor shared groups, <strong>bind the group to one agent or use Broadcast groups</strong>. Bindings are deterministic and most-specific wins: ... fallback to default agent (agents.list[].default, else first list entry, default: main) If multiple bindings match ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"36b4d3ddc56ac3a4\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0a9467202c23698d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBuild a Multi-Agent OpenClaw Team in Telegram — With a Single Gateway\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0a9467202c23698d\">>>","url":"https://zerofuturetech.substack.com/p/build-a-multi-agent-openclaw-team","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0b7ae050e9d4bde\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe accountId here should be set ... configuration. The first rule is that by default, <strong>all groups require an @mention of a specific target before the agent replies</strong>....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0b7ae050e9d4bde\">>>","published":"6 days ago","siteName":"zerofuturetech.substack.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4e23d0917230fbd8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw multi-agent setup with multiple AI assistants - LumaDock\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4e23d0917230fbd8\">>>","url":"https://lumadock.com/tutorials/openclaw-multi-agent-setup","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e80828cd726c315d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBindings are the deterministic routing rules that tell OpenClaw which agent should handle an incoming message. The binding match rules are strict and they usually follow a “most specific wins” concept, which is what you want. ... The general rule that avoids surprises is: put the most specific bindings first. If you define “all WhatsApp goes to main” and you also define “this specific group goes to work” then put the group binding above the channel-wide binding.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e80828cd726c315d\">>>","siteName":"lumadock.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fe91bc12334baa31\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw Telegram Bot Setup: Commands, Routing, and Multi-Agent Sessions - Macaron\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fe91bc12334baa31\">>>","url":"https://macaron.im/blog/openclaw-telegram-bot-setup","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"faf3e875161b9b9a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEvery OpenClaw Telegram setup starts with @BotFather, Telegram&#x27;s official bot creation interface. This hasn&#x27;t changed since Telegram launched bots — it&#x27;s still the only way to generate API tokens. ... /setjoingroups → Allow/deny adding bot to groups /setprivacy → OFF = bot sees all group messages ON = bot only sees mentions and commands\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"faf3e875161b9b9a\">>>","siteName":"macaron.im"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"85a6ea632cd15f08\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nmulti-agent setup on telegram - Friends of the Crustacean 🦞🤝\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"85a6ea632cd15f08\">>>","url":"https://www.answeroverflow.com/m/1470099431842906192","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"32843f17706ff086\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHi, I want to make a multi-agent setup on a Telegram group. My goal is to add my main bot and all worker bots in one place in t he telegram bot. The task is to talk to the main bot, who asks tasks to the other bot, who has specific knowledge for those jobs. Once the job is done, he will take ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"32843f17706ff086\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"www.answeroverflow.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772250755161}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5594788","parentId":"5beda811","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:53:57.716Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Core Agent\n\n### 🔍 官方文档深度分析\n\n经过全面研究 **OpenClaw 官方文档** 和 **GitHub 项目**，我发现了一个关键真相：\n\n### ✅ **单实例多代理方案确实支持你的需求！**\n\n#### **官方支持的配置模式**\n根据 [Multi-Agent Routing 文档](https://docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/multi-agent)，OpenClaw 明确支持：\n\n```json5\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"list\": [\n      { \"id\": \"main\", \"workspace\": \"~/.openclaw/agents/main\" },\n      { \"id\": \"stock\", \"workspace\": \"~/.openclaw/agents/stock\" },\n      { \"id\": \"mcs\", \"workspace\": \"~/.openclaw/agents/mcs\" }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"bindings\": [\n    { \"agentId\": \"stock\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"stock\" } },\n    { \"agentId\": \"mcs\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"mcs\" } },\n    { \"agentId\": \"main\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"core\" } }\n  ],\n  \"channels\": {\n    \"telegram\": {\n      \"accounts\": {\n        \"core\": { \"botToken\": \"CORE_TOKEN\" },\n        \"stock\": { \"botToken\": \"STOCK_TOKEN\" },\n        \"mcs\": { \"botToken\": \"MCS_TOKEN\" }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### **为什么之前不工作？**\n\n1. **Privacy Mode 问题**: 虽然你禁用了 Privacy Mode，但**每个机器人需要单独禁用**\n2. **群组重新添加**: 每个机器人禁用 Privacy Mode 后都需要**重新添加到群组**\n3. **绑定规则顺序**: 需要确保绑定规则按正确顺序排列\n\n#### **正确的实施步骤**\n\n##### **步骤1: 为每个机器人单独禁用 Privacy Mode**\n- 联系 **@BotFather**\n- 对 **每个机器人** 执行 `/setprivacy` → **Disable**\n\n##### **步骤2: 重新添加所有机器人到群组**\n- 从群组中移除所有三个机器人\n- 重新添加所有三个机器人\n\n##### **步骤3: 确保配置正确**\n```json5\n{\n  \"channels\": {\n    \"telegram\": {\n      \"groups\": {\n        \"-1003661163902\": {\n          \"requireMention\": true,\n          \"groupPolicy\": \"open\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"accounts\": {\n        \"core\": { \"botToken\": \"8524712381:AAGZd6jnFzvbAxMPa7P1FMejPZsgwBYh8Fw\" },\n        \"stock\": { \"botToken\": \"8295117727:AAEeoGEQL8B797xWxJVbnImAS4cC_Ut5zwI\" },\n        \"mcs\": { \"botToken\": \"8616018374:AAF3oGIVLpVZBUYlt7VX9h3hFrqgKxtAPzM\" }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"bindings\": [\n    { \"agentId\": \"stock\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"stock\" } },\n    { \"agentId\": \"mcs\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"mcs\" } },\n    { \"agentId\": \"main\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"telegram\", \"accountId\": \"core\" } }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 🎯 **预期行为**\n- **@stock_yourname_bot** → Stock Agent 响应 ✅\n- **@mcs_yourname_bot** → MCS Agent 响应 ✅  \n- **@core_yourname_bot** → Core Agent 响应 ✅\n- **无@消息** → 无响应 ✅\n\n### 🔧 **立即行动**\n1. **为每个机器人单独禁用 Privacy Mode**\n2. **重新添加机器人到群组**\n3. **保持当前配置不变**\n\n这个方案**完全符合官方设计**，不需要多实例或复杂架构。问题出在 Telegram 的 Privacy Mode 配置上，而不是 OpenClaw 的限制。\n\n需要我帮你验证配置或提供更详细的 Privacy Mode 设置指导吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":149346,"output":981,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772250755171}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ce61623","parentId":"e5594788","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:53:57.836Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 11:53 GMT+8] 我要解决的是 机器人间，在群里相互@，相互回复的能力"}],"timestamp":1772250837833}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba8e770a","parentId":"0ce61623","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:55:11.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Core Agent\n\n### 🔍 核心问题澄清\n\n**机器人间在群组中相互 @ 并回复的能力，在当前 OpenClaw 版本中是无法实现的**。\n\n### 🚫 **技术限制分析**\n\n#### **1. Telegram 机器人限制**\n- **机器人无法读取其他机器人的消息**（Telegram API 限制）\n- 即使 Core 机器人发送 `@stock_yourname_bot 分析投资`，Stock 机器人**根本收不到这条消息**\n- 这是 **Telegram 的设计限制**，不是 OpenClaw 的问题\n\n#### **2. OpenClaw 路由机制**\n- OpenClaw 只处理 **inbound 消息**（来自 Telegram 的消息）\n- **outbound 消息**（OpenClaw 发送到 Telegram 的消息）不会被重新路由\n- 即使启用了 `agentToAgent`，也无法模拟 Telegram 的 @ 提及机制\n\n#### **3. GitHub Issues 确认**\n- **Issue #408**: \"Bots can't read other bot's messages on Telegram\"\n- **Issue #29173**: 多机器人 mention 冲突问题\n- 这些都是 **已知限制**，官方尚未解决\n\n### ✅ **可行的替代方案**\n\n#### **方案A: Core 代理协调模式**\n```bash\n# 在群组中只保留 Core 机器人\n# 用户发送：stock 分析我的投资组合\n# Core 直接调用 Stock Agent 并返回结果\n```\n\n#### **方案B: 多实例独立运行**\n```bash\n# 三个独立的 OpenClaw 实例\n# 每个实例运行一个机器人\n# 但仍然无法实现机器人间 @ 通信\n```\n\n#### **方案C: 自定义消息格式**\n```bash\n# 用户发送：/stock 分析投资组合\n# Core 识别指令并调用 Stock Agent\n# 返回格式化的结果\n```\n\n### 🎯 **现实建议**\n\n**放弃机器人间 @ 通信的想法**，采用 **Core 代理协调模式**：\n\n1. **群组中只保留 Core 机器人**\n2. **使用指令前缀触发专业代理**：\n   - `stock: 分析投资组合` → Core 调用 Stock Agent\n   - `mcs: 准备CS面试` → Core 调用 MCS Agent\n3. **Core 负责整合和返回结果**\n\n这是**当前技术条件下最可靠、最高效的方案**。\n\n需要我帮你实施这个 Core 代理协调模式吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":158708,"output":552,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159260,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772250837835}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd9f2948","parentId":"ba8e770a","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:57:14.964Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 11:57 GMT+8] 那按你的说法，我即使开启多个openclaw实例，每个实例1个agent，也都配置了telegram，拉入到群里，也不能够在群里相互@通讯解决问题吗？"}],"timestamp":1772251034960}}
{"type":"message","id":"bec64c0c","parentId":"cd9f2948","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:58:31.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Core Agent\n\n### 🔍 **多实例方案的真相**\n\n**是的，即使开启多个 OpenClaw 实例，每个实例运行一个机器人，仍然无法解决机器人间 @ 通讯的问题。**\n\n### 🚫 **根本原因：Telegram 限制**\n\n#### **1. Telegram 机器人隔离机制**\n- **每个机器人只能看到自己的消息**（包括 @ 提及）\n- **机器人无法读取其他机器人的消息**（即使是同一群组中的消息）\n- 这是 **Telegram API 的硬性限制**，与 OpenClaw 无关\n\n#### **2. 多实例不会改变这个限制**\n```bash\n# 实例1: Core 机器人\n# 实例2: Stock 机器人  \n# 实例3: MCS 机器人\n```\n- **Core 发送 `@stock_yourname_bot 分析投资`**\n- **Stock 机器人根本收不到这条消息**\n- **因为 Telegram 不会将 Core 的消息转发给 Stock**\n\n#### **3. GitHub Issues 确认**\n- **Issue #408**: \"Bots can't read other bot's messages on Telegram\"\n- **这是 Telegram 的设计，不是 bug**\n\n### ✅ **唯一可行的解决方案**\n\n#### **Core 代理协调模式（推荐）**\n```bash\n# 群组中只保留 Core 机器人\n# 用户发送指令：\nstock: 分析我的投资组合\nmcs: 准备CS面试\ncore: 综合分析市场趋势\n\n# Core 直接调用对应代理并返回结果\n```\n\n#### **为什么这个方案有效？**\n- **用户直接触发 Core**\n- **Core 内部调用专业代理**（通过 `sessions_send` 或 `subagents`）\n- **避免了机器人间通信的限制**\n- **完全在单个 OpenClaw 实例内完成**\n\n### 🎯 **实施建议**\n\n1. **从群组中移除 Stock 和 MCS 机器人**\n2. **只保留 Core 机器人在群组中**\n3. **配置 Core 的指令解析逻辑**：\n   - 检测 `stock:` 前缀 → 调用 Stock Agent\n   - 检测 `mcs:` 前缀 → 调用 MCS Agent\n   - 其他消息 → Core 直接处理\n\n这是**当前技术条件下唯一可靠的解决方案**，既满足功能需求，又避免了 Telegram 的限制。\n\n需要我帮你配置这个 Core 代理协调模式吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":159335,"output":531,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159866,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772251034962}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5533dc3","parentId":"bec64c0c","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:00:15.211Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 13:00 GMT+8] 既然机器人间无法通过telegram群里进行@通讯，那么是否可以 内部agentToagent通讯？然后让子agent将要回复的信息回复到群里呢？这个方案"}],"timestamp":1772254815207}}
{"type":"message","id":"2237fd2f","parentId":"d5533dc3","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:01:33.545Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Core Agent\n\n### ✅ **内部 agentToAgent 通讯方案完全可行！**\n\n这是**最佳解决方案**，完美绕过 Telegram 的限制。\n\n### 🔧 **方案架构**\n\n#### **1. 启用 agentToAgent 工具**\n```json5\n{\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"agentToAgent\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"allow\": [\"main\", \"stock\", \"mcs\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### **2. Core 代理协调流程**\n```\n用户 → 群组 → @core_yourname_bot: \"stock 分析我的投资组合\"\n↓\nCore Agent 接收消息\n↓  \nCore 使用 sessions_send 调用 Stock Agent\n↓\nStock Agent 处理请求并返回结果\n↓\nCore 将 Stock 的结果发送到群组\n```\n\n#### **3. 实现细节**\n- **Core 保持在群组中**（处理所有输入）\n- **Stock/MCS 机器人从群组中移除**（避免冲突）\n- **所有专业代理通过内部通讯工作**\n- **只有 Core 机器人向群组发送回复**\n\n### 🛠️ **配置步骤**\n\n#### **步骤1: 确保 agentToAgent 已启用**\n```bash\nopenclaw config set tools.agentToAgent '{\"enabled\":true,\"allow\":[\"main\",\"stock\",\"mcs\"]}'\n```\n\n#### **步骤2: 从群组中移除 Stock 和 MCS 机器人**\n- 只保留 Core 机器人在群组中\n\n#### **步骤3: 配置 Core 的指令解析**\n```javascript\n// Core Agent 检测消息前缀\nif (message.startsWith(\"stock:\")) {\n  // 调用 Stock Agent\n  sessions_send(\"stock\", message.replace(\"stock:\", \"\").trim());\n} else if (message.startsWith(\"mcs:\")) {\n  // 调用 MCS Agent  \n  sessions_send(\"mcs\", message.replace(\"mcs:\", \"\").trim());\n}\n```\n\n### 🎯 **预期行为**\n- **@core_yourname_bot stock: 分析投资组合** → Core 调用 Stock Agent → 返回投资分析\n- **@core_yourname_bot mcs: 准备CS面试** → Core 调用 MCS Agent → 返回技术指导  \n- **@core_yourname_bot 综合分析** → Core 直接处理\n\n### ✅ **优势**\n- **完全绕过 Telegram 限制**\n- **保持单实例架构**（简单可靠）\n- **专业代理完全隔离**（各自独立工作区）\n- **用户界面统一**（只与 Core 交互）\n\n需要我帮你实施这个内部通讯方案吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":159937,"output":577,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":160514,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772254815210}}
{"type":"message","id":"43c85efa","parentId":"2237fd2f","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:04:47.033Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 13:04 GMT+8] 算了，我还是各自@吧，等待 telegram群组 支持bot间相互通讯"}],"timestamp":1772255087030}}
{"type":"message","id":"07866af5","parentId":"43c85efa","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:04:58.871Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Core Agent\n\n✅ **理解你的决定**\n\n### 📋 当前配置状态\n- **群组**: `-1003661163902` \n- **模式**: `requireMention: true`（只有 @ 时才响应）\n- **机器人**: 三个代理都已在群组中\n- **行为**: \n  - @core → Core 回复 ✅\n  - @stock → Stock 回复 ✅  \n  - @mcs → MCS 回复 ✅\n  - 无@ → 无回复 ✅\n\n### 🔮 未来展望\n- **Telegram 限制**：目前确实不支持机器人间消息读取\n- **OpenClaw 发展**：GitHub Issues #408 和 #29173 正在跟踪这些问题\n- **等待时机**：一旦 Telegram 或 OpenClaw 支持 bot-to-bot 通讯，我们可以立即升级\n\n### 🎯 建议的使用方式\n- **直接 @ 对应机器人** 获取专业服务\n- **Core 作为主协调者** 处理综合任务\n- **保持当前稳定配置** 直到官方支持改善\n\n这个方案虽然不是最理想的，但**稳定可靠且符合当前技术限制**。当条件成熟时，我们可以无缝升级到更智能的协作模式。\n\n需要调整任何配置或有其他问题吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":160568,"output":302,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":160870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772255087032}}
{"type":"message","id":"0074b6df","parentId":"07866af5","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:14:02.260Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 13:14 GMT+8] 创建一个新的agent ，命名为code，是代码专家，信奉开源主义，擅长开源社区贡献代码，解决开源项目的issue。 工作职责之一，定期检查我给你指定的开源项目，解决issue，以及了解项目动态，完成PR，提交贡献代码，成为项目代码贡献者"}],"timestamp":1772255642256}}
