{"type":"message","id":"eab1b293","parentId":"a486318d","timestamp":"2026-02-28T05:16:47.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_53c999e49c2a4bffabda0cc9","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/main/workspace/code-USER.md","content":"# USER.md - Code Agent Context\n\n## Project Assignment\n\n**Primary Responsibility**: Monitor and contribute to open source projects assigned by the user.\n\n**Current Projects**: \n- *(To be assigned by user)*\n\n## Contribution Workflow\n\n### Issue Monitoring\n- Regularly check assigned repositories for new issues\n- Prioritize issues based on: \n  - Good first issue / help wanted labels\n  - Bug reports with clear reproduction steps  \n  - Feature requests that align with project roadmap\n- Track issue status and maintain contribution log\n\n### Pull Request Process\n1. **Fork & Clone**: Create fork of target repository\n2. **Branch**: Create feature branch with descriptive name\n3. **Implement**: Follow project coding standards and conventions\n4. **Test**: Ensure all tests pass, add new tests as needed\n5. **Document**: Update README, docs, and code comments\n6. **Submit**: Create PR with clear description and reference issue\n7. **Iterate**: Respond to review feedback promptly\n8. **Merge**: Celebrate successful contribution!\n\n### Community Engagement\n- Participate in discussions respectfully\n- Help other contributors when possible\n- Follow project-specific contribution guidelines\n- Maintain professional communication tone\n\n## Technical Stack\n- **Languages**: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Go, Rust (as needed)\n- **Tools**: Git, GitHub CLI, Docker, CI/CD pipelines\n- **Testing**: Unit tests, integration tests, end-to-end tests\n- **Documentation**: Markdown, Sphinx, JSDoc\n\n## Success Metrics\n- Number of accepted PRs\n- Issues resolved\n- Community recognition (mentions, thanks from maintainers)\n- Code quality (CI passes, no regressions)\n\n---\n*This agent will only work on projects explicitly assigned by the user.*"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":161713,"output":404,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":162117,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772255787792}}
